ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject

ElementDescription: Please think about the most important problem or stressful situation you have experienced in the last 12 months (for example, troubles with a relative or friend, the illness or death of a relative or friend, an accident or illness, financial or work problems); please describe the problem or situation:
Have you ever faced a problem like this before?
Notes: 1= Definitely No (DN); 2= Mainly No (MN); 3= Mainly Yes (MY); 4= Definitely Yes (DY)

ElementDescription: Did you know this problem was going to occur?
Notes: 1= Definitely No (DN); 2= Mainly No (MN); 3= Mainly Yes (MY); 4= Definitely Yes (DY)

ElementDescription: Did you have enough time to get ready to handle this problem?

ElementDescription: When this problem occurred, did you think of it as a threat?

ElementDescription: Please select which thought you would like to challenge
Notes: 1 = Things are never going to get better for me; 2 = I think people do not like me; 3 = I am going to feel stressed and anxious forever; 4 = I can never do anything right; 5 = I am not feeling well. I think I have COVID; 6 = Things are not as fun as they used to be; 7 = I can not catch a break, nothing ever goes my way; 8 = My life is a mess; 9 = I do not have anything to look forward to in life; 10 = I am worthless; 11 = I am a failure; 12 = I would not be able to do it right, so why bother?; 13 = Everyone thinks I am stupid; 14 = I will never be able to change; 15 = I can not control my anger

ElementDescription: You would like to challenge the thought selected - How accurate or true do you think this thought is?
